{"type":"message","id":"0794e605","parentId":"a52ff591","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:18:46.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very revealing:1. **Root `src/main/`** - Only has `index.ts` (424 lines, 11649 bytes). NO `aiService.ts` and NO `backupService.ts`!   - But `index.ts` does `require('./aiService')` and `require('./backupService')` - these files DON'T EXIST in the root src/main!   - This means the root app's main process is BROKEN - it can't start properly because those modules are missing2. **`novel-desktop-app/src/main/`** - Has full implementation:   - `aiService.ts` (22247 bytes)\n   - `backupService.ts` (5813 bytes)   - `index.ts` (11649 bytes - same as root, which is the entry point)\n   - `main.ts` (18172 bytes - the real main logic)   - `preload.ts` (8417 bytes)\n\n3. **Dist size comparison**:   - `novel-desktop-app/dist/`: 26MB (fully built!)   - `dist/`: 12KB (barely anything built!)\n\nSo the real, working, fully-built Electron app is `novel-desktop-app/`, while the root directory app is incomplete and broken - it can't actually run because the compiled main process (dist/main/index.js) references modules that were never compiled.\n\nI missed a critical detail in my earlier review - the root app's preload is only 741 bytes, which is suspiciously small. I need to verify whether the preload was properly compiled or if it's also broken.","thinkingSignature":"36da0116061fcbb244fd71233e2c7b400597b5732c48ea718ec06f64a138a43d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nrd527xx6b0l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/dist/preload/index.js"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nrd527xx6b0l_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/preload/index.ts | wc -l && cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/preload/index.ts | tail -50"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nrd527xx6b0l_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/m