{"type":"message","id":"c9c41aef","parentId":"10106e70","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:20:47.333Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, now I understand the architecture much better:\n\n1. **novel-desktop-app** uses a different build approach:   - Vite builds the renderer (frontend) into `dist/renderer/assets/`\n   - But the Electron **main process** is NOT built - there's no `main.js` in `dist/`\n   - The `package.json` says main is `dist/main/src/main/main.js` which doesn't exist\n   - So this is ALSO BROKEN as a packaged Electron app\n\n2. However, there's a `vite.config.ts` that references `src/renderer` as root, and the `index.html` is at `src/renderer/index.html`\n   \nSo both apps are actually broken in their packaged form. The root app has a main process but no renderer, while novel-desktop-app has the renderer built out but the main process entry point is missing entirely. The vite config confirms the renderer is properly built to `dist/`, but that doesn't matter if the Electron main process can't locate its entry point.\n\nThe real issues are: root's dist is missing both the renderer HTML and compiled preload, novel-desktop-app is pointing to a main process file that doesn't exist, and neither app actually runs. Beyond that, I should check whether EPUB export exists at all, what the build-vector-index script actually does, if there's any vector search implementation, and whether the preload versions are actually mismatched or if I'm seeing old compiled code.","thinkingSignature":"6fa7f5054812d77aa1da4067254ecc73f7d61547ba89762887b666ffcc42bf7c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tl8da5txqk7m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/build-vector-index.js 2>/dev/null | head -80"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tl8da5txqk7m_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"epub\\|markdown.*export\\|export.*chapter\\|download.*chapter\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/sr