{"type":"message","id":"944a8810","parentId":"d9fd4194","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:22:44.492Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the `tsconfig.node.json` which has `outDir: dist/main`. So `tsc -p tsconfig.node.json` should compile `src/main/*.ts` into `dist/main/*.js`. But the `package.json` says `\"main\": \"dist/main/src/main/main.js\"` which is wrong. The actual compiled file would be at `dist/main/main.js` (since `rootDir: \"src/main\"` would give `dist/main/main/main.js` - no wait, `rootDir: \"src\"` means the file structure is preserved... let me think).\n\nActually with `rootDir: \"src\"` and `include: [\"src/main\"]`, the output would preserve the directory structure. So `src/main/main.ts` → `dist/main/main/main.js`. That's why the package.json has `dist/main/src/main/main.js`.\n\n\nBut that path doesn't actually exist, so let me verify the main.ts file more carefully.","thinkingSignature":"43b712aa03bde9124e0d6a5dbe073b436a9ab0512e041eab01f61567d3474c40"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hd81gmy2wi4q_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist -name \"main*.js\" 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hd81gmy2wi4q_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/index.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hd81gmy2wi4q_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/main.ts | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48658,"output":326,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68246,"cost":{"input":0.0145974,"output":0.00039119999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01614432}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776082953998,"responseId":"062c13096b8e052516969e360cafb5f3"}}
