{"type":"message","id":"a5b5d4e4","parentId":"61b350e2","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:23:18.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the key issue with the preload - there are TWO preload files:\n1. `/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/preload.ts` - This one is referenced in `main.ts` as `path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js')`\n2. `/mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/preload/index.ts` - This one is the standalone preload entry point\n\nThese are DIFFERENT files! The `main.ts` in `src/main/` references `path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js')` which would be at `dist/main/preload.js`. But the `tsconfig.node.json` compiles from `src/main` to `dist/main`, so it would compile `src/main/preload.ts` to `dist/main/preload.js`. \n\nBut there's actually a third preload location - the root `src/preload/index.ts` that I found earlier. Let me trace through the build config more carefully. The root `package.json` has its own build setup, and there's also `vite.config.ts` in the root. I need to understand which preload actually gets used when the app runs.\n\nLet me check what's actually in the root `src/renderer/` to see if it differs from `novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/`.","thinkingSignature":"78fcdf70a6f7473871c372bdf199ab04f2ec159da190b1f94820e478427afd66"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_73luta8tqxld_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no src/renderer in root\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_73luta8tqxld_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no src/renderer/src in root\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_73luta8tqxld_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/main/index.ts | grep \"preload\\|require\\|aiService\\|backup\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57427,"output":422,"cacheRea