n't be there.\n\nActually wait - let me re-examine. The root `dist/main/index.js` is the OLD compiled file. It has 128 lines. It probably doesn't have the AI handlers at all. So the root app would start but AI wouldn't work.\n\nFor `novel-desktop-app`:- `package.json` says `main: \"dist/main/src/main/main.js\"` which doesn't exist\n- So if you try to run `electron .` in `novel-desktop-app/`, it will fail immediately\n\nOK so the bottom line is:\n- Root app: main entry point WORKS (128-line version), but it's the old version without AI handlers\n- `novel-desktop-app`: main entry point doesn't exist, can't start\n\nLet me now do a final check - the key issue is whether the ROOT app's renderer has all the right API calls.\n\nI should look at the root `src/renderer/src/App.tsx` to see what APIs it's actually using.","thinkingSignature":"d7b84e6abdcd5de7f4986c3be6f05ae93e2cba0ad286d5474ed64cdb0a1f6429"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mdk6p30e4usi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/App.tsx"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mdk6p30e4usi_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/App.tsx | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61780,"output":703,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81745,"cost":{"input":0.018534,"output":0.0008436,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.020533319999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776083030005,"responseId":"062c1355c2dac0ab3fe0150db3da0fb7"}}
