{"type":"message","id":"e065c8b8","parentId":"41c3b0b6","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:24:39.668Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the critical difference between `main.ts` and `index.ts`:\n\n`main.ts` (the real working one in `novel-desktop-app`):\n- Uses `await import('./aiService.js')` and `await import('./backupService.js')` (dynamic imports)\n- Uses `await import('electron-store')` (dynamic imports)\n- Has the ACTUAL window creation logic and IPC handlers\n\n`index.ts` (the wrapper in `novel-desktop-app`):\n- Uses `require('./aiService')` and `require('./backupService')` (CommonJS)\n- Just re-exports from `startApp` and calls `startApp`\n\n\n- But it's referencing the wrong preload path and using synchronous requires instead of dynamic imports, so it won't work properly\n\nThe real issue is that `main.ts` is the actual entry point in `package.json`, yet it references a preload path that doesn't exist, and the dynamic imports should handle missing modules gracefully unlike the synchronous requires in `index.ts`.\n\nLet me trace through the `main.ts` file more carefully to understand the exact sequence of what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"ef9744e4fbb547e7d5e1a5bf73cbdf79bc77cadc866bef9e8056c68ba5cb6c17"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jy9wa480luuz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/main.ts | wc -l"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jy9wa480luuz_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"startApp\\|createWindow\\|app.whenReady\\|loadURL\\|loadFile\\|setupIpc\\|main entry\\|index.ts\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/main.ts | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65088,"output":344,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84694,"cost":{"input":0.0195264,"output":0.0004128,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02109492}},"stopReason":"