{"type":"message","id":"24221794","parentId":"bcfb5964","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:25:01.048Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `dist/index.html` exists. That's at the root of the `dist/` folder. The main.ts loads:\n- Dev: `http://localhost:3000` (using the vite dev server)\n- Prod: `path.join(__dirname, '../../../index.html')` = `dist/index.html`\n\nNow `dist/index.html` was from the vite build. Let me check its content:\n```html<script type=\"module\" crossorigin src=\"./assets/index-8a975477.js\"></script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"./assets/index-7e8e3dc8.css\">```\n\nSo this loads `assets/index-*.js`. \n\nBut there's also `dist/renderer/index.html` which would load `renderer/assets/index-*.js` from the `simple` config. These are two separate builds with different entry points and asset paths.\n\nThe core issue is that `package.json` points to `dist/main/src/main/main.js` which doesn't exist, so the app can't start even though the renderer builds are there. Meanwhile the root version has its own renderer setup at `src/renderer/` with a basic Workbench, but it's incomplete.\n\nThe real problem is that `main.ts` uses dynamic imports with `.js` extensions (`import('./aiService.js')`), but TypeScript files don't have extensions in the output—the compiled JavaScript files would need to match exactly what it's looking for, and I need to check how the TypeScript config actually handles this.","thinkingSignature":"a8d0d561ccf32f53c2713ccbd2c504367079f6225e8d1c4a5c674bca76608612"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y90ast5z1xm7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"moduleResolution\\|esModuleInterop\\|module\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/tsconfig.node.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y90ast5z1xm7_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"import.*aiService\\|import.*backupService\\|dynamic import\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/main.ts | head -20"}}],"api":"ant