{"type":"message","id":"ccb89660","parentId":"ad4ecfa7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:25:26.814Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `tsconfig.node.json` has `\"module\": \"Node16\"` and `\"moduleResolution\": \"node16\"`. With `Node16` module resolution, when TypeScript compiles `import './aiService.js'`, it would be output as-is (since Node16 handles .js extensions in imports). So the dynamic imports with `.js` extension should work fine in the compiled output.\n\nOK so I think I now have a thorough understanding. Let me summarize all the critical findings:\n\n## Complete Critical Issues Found\n\n### 1. Build流程问题（核心阻塞）\n\n\nThe `package.json` points to a non-existent compiled file at `dist/main/src/main/main.js` when the actual compiled output would be at `dist/main/main.js`. The `build:main` script doesn't run automatically as part of the standard build pipeline, and even if it did, the path mismatch would still cause issues.\n\n### 2. 两套代码重复\nThere's duplicate source code scattered across the repository — the root level and the `novel-desktop-app` directory each have their own `src/main/`, `src/preload/`, and `src/renderer/` directories at different stages of completeness. The root `src/main/index.ts` references service modules that don't exist, and only the root `src/preload/index.ts` has the complete API. The renderer at root has basic components while `novel-desktop-app` has the full implementation, but these two builds are incompatible with each other.\n\n### 3. 依赖包缺失\n`novel-desktop-app/package.json` is missing critical dependencies like `electron-store` and `graphology` that are actually used in the codebase, while the root has these packages but they're in its own `node_modules/`. Additionally, packages like `better-sqlite3` are referenced in code but missing from both projects entirely.\n\n### 4. App启动问题\nThe `novel-desktop-app` can't start because its entry point file doesn't exist, and even if the main process did compile, the HTML loading path would resolve incorrectly.\n\nThe root-level app is equally broken—it would start with an outdated main process that lacks AI functionality, the renderer wouldn't load since the dist folder is incomplete, and any preload script mismatches would cause IPC failures.\n\n### 5. 数据层问题\nThe database implementation has fundamental issues: the SQLite approach in `db/index.ts` would require native module support, but there's no actual SQLite implementation, and the fact extractor is trying to route SQL operations through an AI service rather than a proper database driver.\n\n### 6. 路由和加载路径问题\nThe window creation code loads from `http://localhost:3000` in development, but the actual dev server runs on port 3004, creating a mismatch between where the app expects to find resources and where they're actually served.\n\n### 7. Vite配置分歧\nThe project has two conflicting Vite configs — the original `vite.config.ts` sets the root to `src/renderer` with a proxy for port 5173, while `vite.simple.config.ts` also targets `src/renderer` but uses port 3004 instead. The `dev` script references the simple config, which means the proxy setup from the original config isn't being used.\n\n### 8. 缺少Electron Builder配置\nThe package configuration is missing the necessary settings for packaging the Electron app properly.\n\n### 9. 后备渲染层不完整\nThe root-level `src/renderer/` has its own `db/index.ts` for handling data operations.","thinkingSignature":"3011a2505c2afe731925dcfc8521ab87fd61e19860f8ee2121864310777530d1"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check one final important thing - the `renderer's db` implementations across both apps:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8g6twmbs4rum_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/db/index.ts"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8g6twmbs4rum_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -30 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/src/renderer/src/db/index.ts"}},{"type":"toolC