{"type":"message","id":"c9d5899f","parentId":"65bdaa0b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:25:57.190Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `main.ts` has:\n- Line 92: `preload: path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js')` - This means preload should be at `dist/main/src/main/preload.js`\n- But wait - the tsconfig.node.json compiles from `src/main` → `dist/main`. So:- `src/main/main.ts` → `dist/main/main.ts` → compiled to `dist/main/main.js`\n- `src/main/preload.ts` → `dist/main/preload.ts` → compiled to `dist/main/preload.js`\n\nWait no - the tsconfig.node.json has `\"rootDir\": \"src\"` (or does it?). \n\nActually, with `\"rootDir\": \"src\"` and `\"outDir\": \"dist/main\"`, the compiled output would preserve the directory structure, so `src/main/main.ts` compiles to `dist/main/main/main.js` and `src/main/preload.ts` compiles to `dist/main/main/preload.js`. But `main.ts` references `preload.js` as a sibling file, which would resolve to `dist/main/main/preload.js` - that should work correctly.\n\nHowever, the `package.json` entry point is `dist/main/src/main/main.js`, which doesn't actually exist. The file would be at `dist/main/main/main.js` instead. Additionally, the icon path in `main.ts` points to `dist/main/src/main/../../assets/icon.ico`, which resolves to `dist/assets/icon.ico`, but the actual icon file is at `novel-desktop-app/assets/icon.ico`. These paths are all misaligned. Let me reconsider the tsconfig settings more carefully to understand how the compilation is actually configured.\n\nWith `\"rootDir\": \"src\"` and `\"outDir\": \"dist/main\"`, the TypeScript compiler preserves the directory structure beneath `src`. So `src/main/main.ts` would output to `dist/main/main/main.ts`, not to `dist/main/src/main/` as the entry point suggests. There's definitely a mismatch here. Let me check what the tsconfig actually specifies to clarify this.","thinkingSignature":"85df8b49ff9830fd11b4f0c610a5aaf276730a2dcb6cbfd20fbe37b03e86b310"},{"typ