{"type":"message","id":"0b2abca9","parentId":"d221065f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T12:26:09.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No `rootDir` specified in `tsconfig.node.json`. TypeScript will infer it from the `include` pattern. With `include: [\"src/main\"]` and no `rootDir`, TypeScript will use the common ancestor of the included files as rootDir. Since all files are under `src/main/`, the rootDir would be `src/`.\n\nSo:\n- `src/main/main.ts` → output to `dist/main/main/main.js` (because rootDir='src' and file is at 'src/main/main.ts')\n- `src/main/preload.ts` → output to `dist/main/main/preload.js`\n\n\n- `src/main/index.ts` → output to `dist/main/main/index.js`\n\nThis means `mainWindow` is looking for the preload script at `dist/main/main/main.js`, but the entry point in package.json points to `dist/main/src/main/main.js` — that's the actual bug right there.\n\nSo the real issues are: the entry point path is wrong, the HTML file loading path is also incorrect, and there's no icon file to be found. The tsconfig also doesn't specify a rootDir, which could cause unexpected behavior. Let me look for any TODO comments or incomplete sections that might be hiding other problems.","thinkingSignature":"3aa56f568f0382d39fdacc2973f39c55b48ebb6e0312fe48e5d73c4614a6d1ef"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_44e38nb7dd7o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"TODO\\|FIXME\\|XXX\\|BUG\\|HACK\\|待实现\\|未完成\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main --include=\"*.ts\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_44e38nb7dd7o_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"TODO\\|FIXME\\|XXX\\|BUG\\|HACK\\|待实现\\|未完成\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src --include=\"*.ts\" --include=\"*.tsx\" 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69217,"output":413,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88892,"cost