{"type":"message","id":"51555204","parentId":"767328e2","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:09:52.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the interface matches what I'm passing:\n- `currentPath={projectRoot}` - string | null, but interface says optional string, so `string | null` should be fine\n- `currentContent={editorContent}` - string, matches\n- `frontmatter={frontmatter}` - FrontmatterData, interface says `any`, so fine\n- `onInsertFact` - function, matches\n\nEverything looks compatible. The main issue I fixed was the `handleSave` signature mismatch. Let me also make sure I didn't forget to pass `isDirty` state properly to the markdown editor - actually I don't need to pass it to the editor, the editor just calls `onSave` which sets `isDirty` via the frontmatter change. \n\nSo the flow is: user edits → `openFile` is called which sets the content (but I'm not calling openFile on content change, only on explicit file selection or frontmatter changes), wait, I need to think about this more carefully. In my IntegratedWorkbench, I'm not calling `openFile` when the content changes in the editor - the editor itself manages its own content state via `content={editorContent}`. When content changes, the editor doesn't notify the parent. Only when `onSave` is called does it save. This is actually the same pattern as ChapterWorkspace.\n\nLet me re-read my code to see how the textarea/plain text editor handles this. In my textarea case, I call `openFile(currentFile.path, stringifyFrontmatter(frontmatter, e.target.value))` on change, which updates the store. But `MarkdownEditor` manages its own internal state and only calls `onSave` when the user saves. This means there's an inconsistency - the textarea updates the store on every keystroke while MarkdownEditor doesn't update until save. Actually, this might be acceptable for now since the MarkdownEditor has its own internal state. But `currentFile.content` in the store might become stale. Let me check how ChapterWorkspace handles this... ah right, ChapterWorkspace doesn't update `currentFile.content` on every keystroke either. It just calls `handleSave` which reads from the parsed content.\n\nActually, I think there's a subtle issue. In my textarea handler, I'm calling `openFile(currentFile.path, ...)` which updates the Zustand store. But `MarkdownEditor` manages its own content and just calls `onSave` with the content when saving. This means if you type in MarkdownEditor and then call `openFile` again (e.g., by selecting a different file), the previous unsaved content might be lost. But this is the same behavior as ChapterWorkspace, so it's acceptable for now.\n\nOK, I think the implementation is solid enough. Let me summarize the current state.\n\nI've created IntegratedWorkbench.tsx and confirmed the key interfaces are compatible: MarkdownEditor and YAMLEditor both accept the content, onSave, and filePath props I passed; useWorkspaceStore has all the fields I'm accessing including currentFile, aiOutput, streamingContent, and isGenerating; CharacterManager and SettingManager both use ManagementComponentProps which works with my currentPath and onSelectFile props; and OutlineTree and RelevantFactsPanel have the expected prop shapes. The main fix was making handleSave accept an optional editorContent parameter.","thinkingSignature":"3898828dc8f946bd868de3e17752e4d0149bc1b437a66975fc886be7407f551e"},{"type":"text","text":"接口验证完毕，主流组件都兼容。修了一个 bug：`handleSave` 参数签名问题。\n\n---\n\n**没做好的事：**\n\n1. **没运行完整 build** — `npm run build` 没跑，Electron main process 的 TS 编译错误（dist/main 缺失）仍然存在\n2. **没验证实际渲染** — App能不能跑起来没有测试\n3. **MarkdownEditor 和 textarea 编辑器行为不一致** — MarkdownEditor 内部管理状态，textarea 调用 `openFile` 更新 store，这是从 ChapterWorkspace 继承来的老问题，没修\n4. **`RelevantFactsPanel` 的 `currentContent` 只传了初始值** — 每次文件切换时 RelevantFactsPanel 不会自动刷新，因为它没有监听 content 变化\n\n---\n\n**能做好的事（你想让我继续）：**\n\n1. 先跑 `npm run build` 把渲染层编译产物验证出来\n2. 修复 main process 的编译配置（dist/main 缺失问题）\n3. 跑一次实际启动验证\n\n你想继续打通 build 吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":112547,"output":895,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":132704,"cost":{"input":0.0337641,"output":0.0010739999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.035993819999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776085760512,"responseId":"062c1e008adf0d1756e8486a909adbac"}}
