{"type":"message","id":"b762cf18","parentId":"19ae3b7d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:15:23.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to make the judgment call and execute each step with thinking before each action. Let me think through this systematically.\n\n**Current state:**\n- `tsconfig.node.json` has `outDir: \"dist/main\"` and `include: [\"src/main\"]`\n- TypeScript infers `rootDir: \"src\"` (not `src/main`)\n- Output goes to `dist/main/src/main/main.js`\n- But `package.json` says `\"main\": \"dist/main/src/main/main.js\"` - which actually MATCHES\n\nWait, let me re-check. If `rootDir: \"src\"` and `include: [\"src/main\"]`, then:\n\n\n- Source file: `src/main/main.ts`\n- Output: `dist/main/src/main/main.js`\n\nThat path is correct! But `npm run build:main` has never been run successfully, so `dist/main/src/main/main.js` doesn't actually exist. The 128-line version in `dist/main/index.js` is from a different build configuration that compiled directly from `src/main/index.ts` using the root `tsconfig.main.json` instead. So there are two separate TypeScript configurations at play here, and the older one was used to create that stub.\n\nLooking at the actual issue: `tsconfig.node.json` has `composite: true` with `outDir: \"dist/main\"` and `include: [\"src/main\"]`, but `composite: true` requires all files in `include` to be under `rootDir`. TypeScript is likely complaining about this mismatch or the outDir configuration not working as expected.\n\nLet me just run the build command and see what specific errors surface, then fix them based on what's actually broken rather than guessing at the configuration.","thinkingSignature":"c22c4fe812e3c56e76c8590f3098cee2a0e5d7cec7f6044eeab10fc3e083c4ee"},{"type":"text","text":"好，我来做判断。\n\n**第一步判断：直接跑 `npm run build:main`，用实际错误驱动修复。**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uhhltdkjwy7r_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app && n