{"type":"message","id":"86cef569","parentId":"dc5e2c53","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:29:56.498Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The esbuild version mismatch is still happening on Windows. I upgraded esbuild to latest on WSL2 side, but the Windows node_modules still has the old version. I need to have the user reinstall esbuild on the Windows side.\n\nThe issue is that `npm install esbuild@latest` was run in WSL2 (Linux), but the user is running on Windows. The node_modules are shared on the D: drive between WSL2 and Windows... actually no, WSL2 mounts D: drive too. But the npm install was run in WSL2's bash environment.\n\nWait - the project is on `/mnt/d/` which is the D: drive mounted in WSL2. \n\nSo when the user runs `npm start` from Windows (CMD or PowerShell), it's using Windows Node.js with the same node_modules folder. The esbuild I upgraded to latest was only in the WSL2 context. For Windows to pick up the upgrade, they'd need to run `npm install esbuild@latest` from the Windows side as well.\n\nThe simplest fix is having them reinstall esbuild directly on Windows through an elevated or admin CMD window to ensure the package gets properly updated in node_modules.","thinkingSignature":"e348c9f534ad5135ec9448ef2fefde05868e9f8f4715e1630255ed3cca8792be"},{"type":"text","text":"esbuild 版本冲突。Windows 这边也需要重新装。\n\n在 Windows 上跑这两条命令：\n\n```\ncd D:\\aafuzhi\\axs\\novel-desktop-app\nnpm install esbuild@latest --save-dev\n```\n\n装完后再跑：\n\n```\nnpm start\n```"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":306,"cacheRead":41423,"cacheWrite":672,"totalTokens":42455,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0003672,"cacheRead":0.0024853799999999997,"cacheWrite":0.000252,"total":0.0031207799999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776086981676,"responseId":"062c22c5fcceec38045e71803125a6e8"}}
