{"type":"message","id":"6b4ddb3c","parentId":"22e46d1c","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:33:23.832Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is clear: `Attempted to register a second handler for 'fs:writeFile'`. This means the IPC handler for `fs:writeFile` is being registered twice. \n\nLooking at the main.js compiled output - it's loading `dist/main/src/main/main.js`. The error is at line 524, which is in the compiled main.js.\n\nThe issue is that both `index.js` and `main.js` in src/main are being compiled to dist/main/src/main/, and both of them might be registering IPC handlers. When electron . runs, it loads main.js which might be importing index.js, leading to duplicate handler registration.\n\nOr more likely: the main.js has some code that registers the fs:writeFile handler, and somewhere else (maybe preload.js or index.js) the same handler is being registered again.\n\n\nI need to check the source files to understand which one is handling the IPC registration and whether both are trying to register the same handlers. I should look at main.ts and index.ts in src/main to understand how they're structured and which one should be the entry point. The package.json points to main.js as the entry, but there might be duplication if index.js is also being loaded and both are registering IPC handlers.","thinkingSignature":"60f404b2b8437647ad7c6434bac859b89f7b43d532a55e67f3e33dd1dff536c3"},{"type":"text","text":"Build 成功，但 Electron 启动时报错：`fs:writeFile` 被注册了两次——说明 `index.js` 和 `main.js` 都在注册同一个 handler。\n\n**诊断：哪个文件注册了这个 handler？**\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g7l1apjbvga8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"fs:writeFile\\|handle.*writeFile\\|ipcMain.handle.*writeFile\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/index.ts 2>/dev/null | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g7l1apjbvga8_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"fs:writeFile\\|handle.*writeFile\\|ipcMain.handle.*writ