{"type":"message","id":"7aac2a06","parentId":"cfd72ed9","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:33:33.352Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both `index.ts` and `main.ts` register `fs:writeFile`. And the package.json points to `dist/main/src/main/main.js` as the entry point. When electron loads main.js, it might also be importing index.js which would cause the duplicate registration.\n\nLet me check how the main.js is structured - does it import index.js? Or are both compiled separately and loaded?\n\nActually, since tsconfig.node.json has `include: [\"src/main\"]`, ALL .ts files in src/main are compiled to dist/main/src/main/. So both main.js and index.js are in the output. But when electron starts, it only loads main.js (as per package.json \"main\" field). The issue might be that main.js internally requires/imports index.js, causing double registration.\n\n\nI need to check what main.js actually requires to understand if index.js is being loaded as a dependency.","thinkingSignature":"cdba0af0cd9d6abf8436d55314ab5815c397fb6e75fe9b63c1ab076b5fe603af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f9wdxxyyudhh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -20 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/main/src/main/main.js"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f9wdxxyyudhh_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"require\\|import\\|index.js\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/main/src/main/main.js | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26388,"output":284,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45934,"cost":{"input":0.007916399999999999,"output":0.0003408,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009412919999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776087203990,"responseId":"062c23a275c1b3a9106c89310ba8c10f"}}
