{"type":"message","id":"393eab0e","parentId":"5dc819b6","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:33:57.289Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_euvse1k4bk5h_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const { deleteBackup } = await import('./backupService.js');\n        const result = deleteBackup(backupPath);\n        return result;\n    }\n    catch (error) {\n        return { success: false, error: error.message };\n    }\n});\n// 写入文件时自动备份\nelectron_1.ipcMain.handle('fs:writeFile', async (event, filePath, content) => {\n    try {\n        // 验证路径\n        const validation = validatePath(filePath);\n        if (!validation.valid) {\n            return { success: false, error: validation.error };\n        }\n        // 确保目录存在\n        const dir = path_1.default.dirname(validation.resolvedPath);\n        if (!fs_1.default.existsSync(dir)) {\n            fs_1.default.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n        }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"const { deleteBackup } = await import('./backupService.js');\n        const result = deleteBackup(backupPath);\n        return result;\n    }\n    catch (error) {\n        return { success: false, error: error.message };\n    }\n});\n// 写入文件时自动备份\nelectron_1.ipcMain.handle('fs:writeFile', async (event, filePath, content) => {\n    try {\n        // 验证路径\n        const validation = validatePath(filePath);\n        if (!validation.valid) {\n            return { success: false, error: validation.error };\n        }\n        // 确保目录存在\n        const dir = path_1.default.dirname(validation.resolvedPath);\n        if (!fs_1.default.existsSync(dir)) {\n            fs_1.default.mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n        }","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776087237280}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b18aea2","parentId":"393eab0e","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:34:08.075Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the error \"Attempted to register a second handler for 'fs:writeFile'\" happens at line 524 of main.js. But if main.js doesn't load index.js, then how is the handler registered twice?\n\nWait, maybe the problem is that BOTH main.js AND index.js get loaded because electron might have some auto-loading mechanism for `index.js` in the same directory as `main.js`?\n\nOr actually - the `dist/main/src/main/` directory has BOTH main.js AND index.js. When electron starts with `main.js` as the entry, maybe something in the electron app loading process also loads `index.js`?\n \nActually, I'm realizing the project has two tsconfig files - there's tsconfig.json for the renderer and tsconfig.node.json for the main process. Both main.ts and index.ts are being compiled to the same output directory, but only one of them should actually be the entry point that Electron loads.\n\nThe real question is whether Electron is somehow loading both files, or if there's duplicate IPC handler registration happening. Let me check if main.ts or main.js is importing or requiring index.js somewhere, which would explain why both handlers are getting registered.","thinkingSignature":"5d3179ef29883d4c78ce28f390bfc8cd99ea8e008b69152a5489cd01e97d714c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_51iibgx2tto3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"require\\|import\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/main/main.ts | grep -v \"node_modules\\|'\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27949,"output":302,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47513,"cost":{"input":0.0083847,"output":0.00036239999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00990282}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776087237291,"responseId":"062c23c502ec77591177