{"type":"message","id":"2d54c110","parentId":"e2b1f4b5","timestamp":"2026-04-13T13:51:15.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue. Looking at line 68: `const [activeMenu, setActiveMenu] = useState('project')` - the default activeMenu is 'project', not 'workspace'. And the workspace case (line 333) is only shown when `activeMenu === 'workspace'`.\n\nSo for the IntegratedWorkbench to show, the user needs to click the \"创作工作台\" menu item in the left sidebar. But the user is asking \"创作工作台呢\" - they might be looking at the app but don't see the \"创作工作台\" menu item.\n\nWait, but looking at line 182: `{ key: 'workspace', icon: <ThunderboltOutlined />, label: '创作工作台' }` - this is in the sidebar menu. \n\nOnce the project opens, the \"创作工作台\" option should appear in the sidebar. When the user switches to it, activeMenu becomes 'workspace' and the IntegratedWorkbench renders. The real issue might be that the project opened but the sidebar hasn't updated to show the workspace option yet, or the user switched to workspace but the content isn't loading properly.\n\nActually, I think I found it—there's probably a Layout structure problem. The outer Layout wraps everything with the header and content area, and when `activeMenu === 'workspace'`, it tries to render the IntegratedWorkbench component. But if the content panel has `height: 'calc(100vh - 120px)'` and the Layout inside is also set to `height: '100vh'`, there's a nested Layout mismatch that's preventing the workspace from displaying correctly.\n\nThe outer Layout uses the full viewport height while the content div uses a calculated height based on the viewport minus the header. This creates a constraint where the workspace component might be getting squeezed or clipped. And looking at the error output the user provided, the mock filesystem loaded from localStorage but there's no indication that `setIsProjectOpen(true)` was ever called, which would explain why the works