{"type":"message","id":"b11f1a5f","parentId":"f48341f7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:08:51.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Build succeeded. Now the user needs to rebuild on Windows. But I also need to think about how to get the updated files to Windows.\n\nThe user has the project on Windows at D:\\aafuzhi\\axs\\novel-desktop-app. I can either:\n1. Tell the user to copy the files over (scp/rsync)\n2. Or the user does a fresh build on Windows\n\nThe Windows side already has the esbuild fix (`npm install esbuild@latest --save-dev`), so if they run `npm start` it will rebuild everything.\n\nBut actually, the WSL build already happened and the dist files are updated. The user could copy the dist files. But the source files in WSL are different from Windows. \n \nThe IntegratedWorkbench.tsx file exists in both locations—WSL at /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/ and Windows at D:\\aafuzhi\\axs\\novel-desktop-app\\. The simplest approach would be syncing the source files from WSL to Windows, though I'm not sure what tools the user has available. Let me just have them rebuild directly on Windows since that's the most straightforward option.\n\nActually, I could use a Git push/pull workflow if the project is version-controlled, or manually sync the specific files that changed. But the most practical solution is probably to just let them run `npm start` on Windows, which will trigger the prestart script to rebuild everything anyway.","thinkingSignature":"d2b8657fbb732b7cb8ad013bf12bf0013f1c9359fe77b9f385399fa1400b0aea"},{"type":"text","text":"Build 成功 ✅。但需要把 WSL 的改动同步到 Windows。\n\n**Windows 上手动同步（最快的办法）：**\n\n打开一个新的 PowerShell，执行：\n\n```powershell\nCopy-Item -Path \"\\\\wsl$\\Ubuntu\\home\\ai\\.openclaw\\workspace\\main\\IntegratedWorkbench.tsx\" -Destination \"D:\\aafuzhi\\axs\\novel-desktop-app\\src\\renderer\\src\\components\\IntegratedWorkbench.tsx\" -Force\n```\n\n然后再跑：\n\n```\nnpm start\n```\n\n这样不用完整重建，直接用 Windows 那边已有的 no