{"type":"message","id":"0d73ef2d","parentId":"8611d0a0","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:48:11.854Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The grep for \"IntegratedWorkbench\" found 0 matches in ALL index JS files! That means the component IS NOT in the built JS!\n\nWait, but the user can see the UI (the left sidebar of icons). If the IntegratedWorkbench wasn't in the bundle, what were they seeing?\n\nOh wait - the grep returned `0` for all files. But we know the build succeeded and the CSS has our changes. And we know the App.tsx imports IntegratedWorkbench...\n\nUnless... the build is NOT using the updated App.tsx! Maybe there's a different entry point or the build is somehow serving a cached version.\n \nAh, I think I see it now - the vite config uses `vite.simple.config.ts`, which might be configured differently than the standard setup. The lazy loading pattern in App.tsx means IntegratedWorkbench could be bundled separately, not in the main index files. I need to check which chunks actually contain the component.","thinkingSignature":"4e453f9b3412aacca61b0a1b7f5049eaefcf527fb1422c2caed7a0f8e764b058"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_87hspe5zca3v_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -l \"IntegratedWorkbench\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/renderer/assets/*.js 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_87hspe5zca3v_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -l \"创作工作台\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/renderer/assets/*.js 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73509,"output":301,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93072,"cost":{"input":0.022052699999999998,"output":0.0003612,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.023569619999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776091680124,"responseId":"062c351f702e49fe34562f7ca3154ca4"}}
