{"type":"message","id":"b0fff44a","parentId":"3529ba63","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:48:24.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the chunk `index-4ce7a73b.js` DOES contain \"创作工作台\". But the `IntegratedWorkbench` grep returned nothing for all files...\n\nWait, the second grep for \"创作工作台\" found it in `index-4ce7a73b.js`. But the first grep for \"IntegratedWorkbench\" returned nothing. This could be because the component name is minified/obfuscated in the bundle. The string \"IntegratedWorkbench\" as a variable name might be renamed during minification.\n\nActually, that's expected. After minification, the component might be renamed to something like `a` or `b`. \n\nSo the \"IntegratedWorkbench\" string wouldn't appear as plain text. But \"创作工作台\" is a Chinese string literal used in JSX, so it would still be present in the bundle. The fact that it's in the chunk means the component IS being bundled. The \"18 modules transformed\" issue the user saw earlier was because that was a cached build from Windows - it only transformed 18 modules since nothing had changed. But we then ran `npm run build` and it showed 4218 modules transformed.\n\nThe real issue is whether that updated bundle is actually reaching the user's Electron window. Either Electron is serving from a different dist folder, or there's caching at the Electron level preventing the fresh build from loading. I should check what the `homepage` or `homepage` field in package.json shows for the renderer entry point, and verify that `index.html` is pointing to the correct bundle. Let me also look at what `vite.simple.config.ts` is actually configured to output.","thinkingSignature":"7e19c131fd7703a1be7b392c5a69c4c5d55fef5db5d58aed522b4b7d612be96a"},{"type":"text","text":"构建产物里有\"创作工作台\"，组件确实打进去了。检查 index.html 是否指向正确路径：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t24zunfxac3b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/renderer