{"type":"message","id":"9dacb322","parentId":"976c77ce","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:53:48.612Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The dist files look correct:\n- index.html references `index-4ce7a73b.js`\n- CSS has `.content-panel` with `display:flex;flex-direction:column`\n\nBut the user said \"又一片空白了\" - completely blank. Previously it was showing the left sidebar (64px icons).\n\nLet me think about what could cause a COMPLETELY blank content area (not just missing right side):\n\n1. IntegratedWorkbench throws an error during render → would show error boundary or blank\n2. The `isProjectOpen || !projectRoot` condition in IntegratedWorkbench is true → shows the \"请先打开一个项目\" placeholder (but this takes 48px padding, not blank)\n\n\n3. A CSS issue hiding everything, or the workspace case not being triggered in App.tsx\n\nWait - the user deleted the dist folder. When `npm start` runs, it triggers `prestart` which runs `npm run build:all`. The build:main completed fine, but vite build might have failed due to the esbuild issue. If the vite build failed, the dist/renderer files would be incomplete or empty, which would explain why everything's blank.\n\nBut the user said it was blank \"after\" running npm start with deleted dist, which means the build succeeded (or seemed to) but the rendering is broken. Actually, wait - they ran `rmdir /s /q dist` and then `npm start`. The `prestart` hook would rebuild, but maybe it failed silently or the fresh build is missing something critical.\n\nLet me reconsider: if the content area is completely blank instead of showing the old three-panel layout with the sidebar, that suggests IntegratedWorkbench is rendering but something's wrong with it. The component has a check for `isProjectOpen || !projectRoot` that would show a placeholder if no project is open, so maybe that's what's being rendered instead of the actual workspace.\n\nBut actually, that placeholder has styling with padding and a centered title - it wouldn't produce a blank screen. So the real issue is likely that IntegratedWorkbench itself is failing to render, either because it's crashing or because the component code has a problem that prevents it from mounting at all.\n\nLet me check if there's a JavaScript error being thrown. The component imports several hooks and utilities like `useWorkspaceStore`, `parseFrontmatter`, and `joinPath` - if any of these are undefined or malformed, it could cause the entire component to fail silently. I should verify that all the imported modules are actually valid and that `joinPath` is properly exported from the utils module.","thinkingSignature":"78478907584922c43ce1d756f3f66346137d0f8290f66abcd1b03d1bfd87f07b"},{"type":"text","text":"dist 存在且 CSS 正确。检查组件是否有运行时问题：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cvgculc1mwkn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"joinPath\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/utils/pathUtils.ts | head -5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cvgculc1mwkn_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"export.*joinPath\\|export default\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/utils/pathUtils.ts | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":75486,"output":658,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95406,"cost":{"input":0.0226458,"output":0.0007896,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02459112}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776092006783,"responseId":"062c3665065e0e7478cf699b0dc7f562"}}
