{"type":"message","id":"98cbe97b","parentId":"c9261fca","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:54:02.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, `joinPath` is exported correctly. Let me check a more critical potential issue - the `useWorkspaceStore` store and its `openFile` action. Actually, I wonder if the issue is that when `isProjectOpen` is false, the IntegratedWorkbench shows a placeholder, but when `isProjectOpen` is true and `projectRoot` is set... the rest of the component renders.But actually, the placeholder with `height: '100vh'` and padding would not produce a \"blank\" screen. It would show the \"🍅 创作工作台\" title and \"请先打开一个项目\" text.Wait - maybe the issue is that the IntegratedWorkbench renders but it's ONLY showing the header (56px) and nothing below. Because the `projectRoot` state might be null or empty, and the check at line:\n\n\n```javascript\nif (!isProjectOpen || !projectRoot) {\n  return (...)\n}\n```\n\nIf `isProjectOpen` is false OR `projectRoot` is null, it shows the placeholder. The placeholder has `height: '100vh'`, so it would show the title text. But the user said \"完全空白\" (completely blank), not \"显示占位符文字\". So the placeholder with its styled div containing centered title and text would be visible, not blank. Maybe the placeholder isn't actually rendering at all and the component is returning something else entirely.\n\nLet me trace through the App.tsx to understand what's actually being rendered. The workspace case has a condition - if `isProjectOpen` is false, it might render something different. Actually, the user deleted the dist folder and ran npm start, which would trigger a fresh build. The build process runs npm install, then build:main and build:renderer. I need to verify whether that fresh build actually completed successfully and whether there were any TypeScript errors that might have prevented the placeholder from rendering properly.","thinkingSignature":"0736e129f0413a9d0b3eba6946510f5dd14eaa7550