{"type":"message","id":"06519b22","parentId":"e8a6813b","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:55:02.367Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"40 occurrences of \"display.*flex\" in the bundle - that makes sense given all the flexbox style code.The fact that the bundle has 40 flex references, the correct CSS with content-panel, and the \"创作工作台\" text means the component IS in the bundle correctly.\n\nSo if the component is correctly built, WHY is the screen completely blank?\n\nLet me think about what could cause a COMPLETELY blank content area:\n\n1. The `IntegratedWorkbench` component throws an error during render (caught by error boundary or React)\n2. The component returns `null` or nothing3. A CSS issue that hides everything4. The component's outer wrapper `div` has `display: none` or `visibility: hidden` due to some condition5. \n\nI'm wondering if the App.tsx has an error boundary wrapping the workspace area, and maybe `IntegratedWorkbench` is throwing an error that's being silently caught. Looking at the source, App.tsx doesn't seem to have an error boundary wrapping the content-panel at all. Let me check what's actually being rendered when the workspace is active - it's just a plain div with the content-panel class and inline styles, containing the `IntegratedWorkbench` component directly.\n\nThe div should render fine even if the component throws an error. But I'm realizing the user deleted the dist folder before running npm start, which triggered a fresh build. The esbuild version mismatch might have caused vite to fail or produce a bad build, though it reported success. Let me check what vite actually reported during that build process.\n\nActually, the esbuild issue was with the standalone binary version mismatch, but vite bundles its own esbuild, so that shouldn't affect the actual build. What if there's a TypeScript error in the IntegratedWorkbench source that vite is silently catching? I should verify the TypeScript validity of the source file to rule that out.\n\nWait, I'm noticing something about the CSS - the minified content-panel styles look correct with flexbox and column direction, but I need to trace through the actual CSS being applied to see if there's a specificity or override issue causing the layout to break.\n\nActually, I'm wondering if the problem is upstream - maybe App.tsx isn't even passing the right props to IntegratedWorkbench, or the component is throwing an error during render that's getting silently swallowed somewhere in the rendering pipeline.\n\nLet me check the actual source file to see what IntegratedWorkbench is doing at runtime, particularly around how it's handling the project state and whether it's returning null or crashing when the project isn't open.","thinkingSignature":"e255f0e43370b10dcab62620680e5cea7e45cd91befd4e9963c588b5b3635459"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kwomy47hbaap_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"wc -l /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/components/IntegratedWorkbench.tsx"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kwomy47hbaap_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/components/IntegratedWorkbench.tsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78300,"output":611,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98173,"cost":{"input":0.02349,"output":0.0007331999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02537892}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776092082279,"responseId":"062c36b08678d39164fa7750f5bf095d"}}
