worse than before when they had the sidebar visible. This suggests something else is wrong with the workspace rendering itself.\n\nLet me think about what could cause a completely white screen. The IntegratedWorkbench component either renders with content or shows a placeholder with a title, but if it's blank that means nothing is rendering at all. Maybe there's an error being thrown silently, or perhaps the Electron app is actually running but displaying a blank window because the React component isn't mounting properly.\n\nWait, I'm realizing the issue might be with the build itself. When the user deleted the dist folder and ran npm start, the build process should have recreated those files with fresh content. But if the build failed or didn't complete properly, Electron would be serving an incomplete or empty page. That would explain why everything went blank after the rebuild attempt.\n\nLet me actually look at what's in the bundled JavaScript file to verify it contains the right content and check if the source files are being included correctly in the build output.","thinkingSignature":"018ca12f716568f2242da687bb617ca71fc91837ddbd447795e6b8549e02b9e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v3xlkysu9jcg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -o \"🍅[^}]*创作工作台\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/dist/renderer/assets/index-4ce7a73b.js | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":79154,"output":649,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99065,"cost":{"input":0.0237462,"output":0.0007788,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025680719999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776092102537,"responseId":"062c36c5ef443a0bf58774c413685218"}}
