{"type":"message","id":"6534b56f","parentId":"6893a517","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:56:01.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file was last modified at 22:51, which is about 4 minutes ago. This matches when the user deleted dist and ran npm start.\n\nOK so the dist files ARE fresh from the rebuild. The bundle has the correct content (3 occurrences of \"🍅 创作工作台\"). The CSS is correct.\n\nSo why is the screen blank?\n\nWait. Let me re-read the user's message: \"又一片空白了\". \"又\" (again) - this word implies the screen went blank AGAIN. Previously it was showing the left sidebar. Now it's blank.This suggests that AFTER the fresh build, the content area became worse (blank instead of partial).\n \nSo what's different between now and the previous run? The user deleted dist and rebuilt, which should have started fresh. But the blank screen is happening even though dist has the correct files now. Maybe Electron is still serving cached files somehow, or the new build itself isn't actually being loaded even though it exists.\n\nLet me think about the App.tsx structure - it uses React.lazy() for dynamic imports and renders through a Suspense wrapper. If IntegratedWorkbench is throwing an error during render, the Suspense fallback would display instead of the actual content, which would explain the blank screen.\n\nBut actually, the user deleted the dist folder, so the old component shouldn't even be there anymore. Unless the user didn't actually run npm start after deleting dist, or the build failed silently without proper error reporting. I need to verify whether the Windows console showed any build errors or if it appeared to succeed.\n\nLooking at the sequence: the user ran the build command, saw some output, then reported the screen went blank again. This suggests the build itself completed (hence the output), but something about the new IntegratedWorkbench component is causing it to fail at runtime rather than during the build phase.\n\nThe real issue might be that IntegratedWorkbench has a problem rendering - maybe it's throwing an error that's being caught by an error boundary, or it's returning null/undefined, or there's a problem with how the component initializes and renders its content. I should check the component's export and whether it's properly connected to the workspace flow. I need to verify that the imported components are actually being used correctly in the render method, and check whether there's a type mismatch or import issue that's causing the blank screen. Let me trace through the component's dependencies - CharacterManager, FactsPanel, and others - to see if any of them might be returning null or failing to render for some reason.\n\nActually, the most direct approach is to check if there are any TypeScript compilation errors in the build output that might be causing this.","thinkingSignature":"37b0e966eb31b6c7dcee2fa62900c600ed2e11bdca328dc8f0de0841a6c1fb78"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kf9jnfsc6leq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app && npx vite build --config vite.simple.config.ts 2>&1 | grep -E \"error|Error|✓|warning\" | head -20","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80566,"output":617,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100445,"cost":{"input":0.024169799999999998,"output":0.0007404,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026065919999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776092142668,"responseId":"062c36eef51fe043791fc37ac1337a1d"}}
