{"type":"message","id":"5d94347e","parentId":"9d7ca476","timestamp":"2026-04-13T14:56:25.857Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's the problem! The esbuild service is stopped (the Windows version mismatch issue). Vite build FAILS with esbuild error. But the dist files exist from a previous successful build (from the WSL build I ran earlier at 22:51).\n\nSo when the user deleted dist and ran npm start on Windows, the vite build FAILED silently (or appeared to fail), but the OLD dist files from the WSL build were still present (from my earlier WSL build at 22:51 which succeeded).\n\nWait, but the user deleted dist. So there should be no dist files. Unless... the user deleted dist but then the build started and created NEW dist files. But those new dist files would be from the FAILED vite build, which would have nothing or broken content.\n \nActually, I think vite clears the dist directory before building, so when the esbuild error occurs mid-build, the old files are already wiped and the new ones aren't fully written. That would explain why the user sees a blank screen—the dist folder exists but contains either nothing or corrupted output from the failed build attempt.\n\nLooking at the timestamps though, the files show an April 13 date from 22:51, which seems off. Let me trace through the timeline: the user deleted dist at some point, ran npm start, and the files appeared. But the timestamp suggests the build might have happened at a different time than expected, or there's something off with how the files were created.\n\nThe real issue is that vite build is failing with the esbuild error \"Cannot start service: Host version mismatch\" - this is the same problem I hit earlier when trying to build in WSL. The Windows environment has this version conflict preventing the build from succeeding, so even though dist was deleted and npm start was run, the actual build process is breaking at the esbuild step.\n\nSince the build fails but the old dist folder still exists from before the deletion, Electron ends up serving stale files from that previous successful build. The new component changes never actually get built into the dist folder because the vite build keeps failing.\n\nThe solution is straightforward—I need to fix the Windows esbuild installation first so the build can actually complete successfully, rather than just repeatedly deleting and rebuilding with broken dependencies.","thinkingSignature":"7fe0c32339ebc714026528bc0db7db64a0f290c233c271e16b6e1bab133ba855"},{"type":"text","text":"找到根本原因了：\n\n**Windows 上的 esbuild 版本冲突导致 vite build 失败**，dist 目录是旧的（来自 WSL 的 22:51 构建），Windows 自己从未成功构建过。\n\nesbuild 错误：`Host version \"0.18.20\" does not match binary version \"0.24.2\"`\n\n这就是为什么每次说\"没变化\"——Windows 根本没能重新 build，用的还是旧文件。\n\n在 Windows PowerShell 执行：\n\n```powershell\ncd D:\\aafuzhi\\axs\\novel-desktop-app\nnpm install esbuild@0.24.2 --save-dev\nnpm start\n```\n\n`0.24.2` 是匹配 Windows electron 包所需的版本，这次指定具体版本号而不是 `latest`。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81212,"output":612,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101086,"cost":{"input":0.0243636,"output":0.0007344,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.026253719999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776092162878,"responseId":"062c3702a905b95dd9ca7b0af624149d"}}
