{"type":"message","id":"7467f3b4","parentId":"c95fa57f","timestamp":"2026-04-13T15:20:52.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, `ManagementComponentProps` has `currentPath: string` and `onSelectFile`. Let me verify IntegratedWorkbench passes `onSelectFile` correctly.\n\nLooking at the IntegratedWorkbench render:\n```tsx\n{activeTab === 'characters' && (\n  <CharacterManager currentPath={projectRoot} onSelectFile={(path) => { openFile(path, ''); setActiveTab('outline') }} />\n)}\n```\n\nBut wait - `CharacterManager.onSelectFile` is called with a relative path like `characters/${character.name}.yaml`, but `openFile` expects an absolute path. \n\nI need to check what `openFile` actually expects in the workspaceStore.","thinkingSignature":"1717b1c5bb30056a22efd930d4967a2bf384032eb51b81821a9be9eb1126bda7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2oxj3x82wwzp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"openFile\\|readFile\" /mnt/d/aafuzhi/axs/novel-desktop-app/src/renderer/src/stores/workspaceStore.ts | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":89804,"output":203,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109269,"cost":{"input":0.0269412,"output":0.00024359999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.028340519999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776093645317,"responseId":"062c3ccc521b4089cd14862bfbb0047f"}}
